race.description: The Baker Group 3Yo Cup 21St November Hcp (C3)
race.comment: Competitive. RUNAWAY STATEMENT (4) switched from the Stokes yard in Adelaide and resumed here with a narrow defeat over 1200m in a CL4. Has strong figures this trip, and the premier hoop stays aboard. Strips fitter and is ready to win. RED SPHERE (1) came back to the turf here and delivered a 60 over 1200m. Has his first crack at the longer sprint but hits the race at peak and the in-form Byrne Burke stays in the saddle. This is a step up, but he has scope for further improvement. IT'S JAGGER TIME (5) was beaten a nose first-up off 303 days and then was on-pace winning a CL1 stepping up to this trip. He will be fitter again and has more up his sleeve. A chance to go back-to-back. KAKIA (2) was an easy winner over this trip third-up jumping favourite. Heading in the right direction and will be fancied to repeat. WHIPPIN PICCADILLY (7) brings strong form from the Devonport synthetic in better grade. He placed his only start here, and it was over this distance.
